Hit.Hit_def: cd05753, Ig2_FcgammaR_like, Second immunoglobulin (Ig)-like domain of Fcgamma-receptors (FcgammaRs) and similar proteins. Ig2_FcgammaR_like: domain similar to the second immunoglobulin (Ig)-like domain of Fcgamma-receptors (FcgammaRs). Interactions between IgG and FcgammaR are important to the initiation of cellular and humoral response. IgG binding to FcgammaR leads to a cascade of signals and ultimately to functions such as antibody-dependent-cellular-cytotoxicity (ADCC), endocytosis, phagocytosis, release of inflammatory mediators, etc. FcgammaR has two Ig-like domains. This group also contains FcepsilonRI, which binds IgE with high affinity.
